        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>1210 Napau Street New York</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Sepr. 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">/The copy of the Occident usually sent to<lb/> the Office of the
                Asmonean has not been received for the<lb/> current month, but my attention has been
                called to an<lb/> editorial article therein, entitled, “<persName>Dr.
                    Wise</persName> and his<lb/> congregation” in which appears the following
                observations:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">“They communicate to us certain doings of the editor<lb/> of the
                latter paper, which we do not choose to<lb/> publish, as we mean not to interfere
                with our<lb/>
                <sic>cotemporary</sic>, for we should at once be taxed<lb/> with wishing to injure
                him, for the sake of<lb/> increasing our circulation, a charge which<lb/> we do not
                    <add>care</add> just now to bring down on us. But<lb/> the acts of baseness
                (which if true, ought to cover<lb/> the perpetrators with everlasting
                infamy/alleged<lb/> to have been committed against <persName>Dr. Wise</persName>, do
                not<lb/> unfortunately contradict the statement which we<lb/> said before the
                public.”</p>
            <p>The inference which has been drawn from the above quoted<lb/> sentences, necessitates
                me to request that you will, at</p>
            <p rend="The following is written in the top left corner of the page.">Editor of<lb/>
                Asmonean<lb/> Re: <persName>Wise</persName>—</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>your earliest convenience, favor me with a statement<lb/> of the “certain doings of
                the Editor of the Asmonean” which<lb/> have been communicated to you, and that you
                will further<lb/> please to state, if you apply the term “acts of baseness” to<lb/>
                any conduct of mine</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">I am dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">Rob Lyons</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
